## Five Sub-Packages Map (Browser + BFF sub-ring)

| Module | May import from | May NOT import from |
|--------|-----------------|---------------------|
| `frontend/lib/wire/` | `zod`, stdlib | Everything else in `frontend/lib/` |
| `frontend/lib/trust-view/` | `zod`, stdlib | Everything else in `frontend/lib/` |
| `frontend/lib/ports/` | `wire/`, `trust-view/` | `adapters/`, `translators/`, `transport/`, `composition.ts` |
| `frontend/lib/translators/` | `wire/`, `trust-view/` | `adapters/`, `ports/`, `transport/`, `composition.ts`, any SDK |
| `frontend/lib/transport/` | `wire/`, stdlib, `EventSource` | `adapters/`, `ports/`, `translators/`, `composition.ts`, any SDK |
| `frontend/lib/adapters/` | `ports/`, `wire/`, `trust-view/`, third-party SDKs | `translators/`, `transport/`, `composition.ts`, other `adapters/` |
| `frontend/lib/composition.ts` | Everything in `frontend/lib/`, React context | Nothing imports composition |

Cross-process rule: `frontend/` MUST NEVER import a Python module.

## Layering Rules (F-Family)

- **F1** Three composition roots, no fourth. `ARCHITECTURE_PROFILE` reads only in `frontend/lib/composition.ts`, `middleware/composition.py`, or `agent_ui_adapter/server.py`.
- **F2** Five sub-packages per process, no sixth. New top-level dir under `frontend/lib/` requires a merged ADR.
- **F3** Substrate swaps are composition-root-only. V2/V3 swap touches exactly one new adapter file + one composition selector update.
- **F4** Frontend ring never imports backend Python at module scope. Cross-process boundary is HTTP/SSE only.

## Wire & Kernel Rules (W-Family)

- **W1** Pure shapes only. No I/O, no logging, no SDK calls in `wire/` or `trust-view/`.
- **W2** Mirror Python source of truth. Every `agent_ui_adapter/wire/` module has a TS twin under `frontend/lib/wire/`. Drift detected via `__python_schema_baseline__.json`.
- **W3** Discriminated unions, not bare unions. Multi-variant types use `z.discriminatedUnion("type", [...])` with `z.literal()` discriminators.
- **W4** Sealed envelopes are read-only. `Readonly<T>` typing; never spread, re-serialize, or add convenience props.
- **W5** `trace_id` is structural. Every event schema extends `BaseEvent` declaring `trace_id: z.string()`.
- **W6** snake_case on the wire; camelCase only after a translator.
- **W7** Schema const + inferred type co-export with same name (e.g., `export const RunCreateRequest` and `export type RunCreateRequest`).
- **W8** `trust-view/` exports only `z.infer<...>` types. No functions or mutable state.

## Port Rules (P-Family)

- **P1** One interface per file.
- **P2** Vendor-neutral name (e.g., `MemoryClient`, not `Mem0Client`).
- **P3** Behavioral contract documented in JSDoc above the interface.
- **P4** Typed errors (`AgentAuthError`, `ThreadStoreError`, `MemoryError`) declared via `@throws`.
- **P5** Async by default; synchronous only with documented justification (e.g., `FeatureFlagProvider.isEnabled()` for render-time reads).
- **P6** No imports from `adapters/`, `translators/`, `transport/`, or `composition.ts`.
- **P7** Ports come paired with a conformance test in `frontend/tests/architecture/test_port_conformance.ts`.

## Adapter Rules (A-Family)

- **A1** SDK imports permitted only here (and in `middleware/adapters/`).
- **A2** Adapters do not import each other. Cross-adapter dependencies injected via composition root as port instances.
- **A3** Depend on `ports/`, `wire/`, `trust-view/`, and SDKs only. No `translators/`, `transport/`, or `composition.ts` imports.
- **A4** SDK types never escape the adapter file. Convert to `wire/` shapes before returning.
- **A5** Error translation table in JSDoc (HTTP status -> typed port error).
- **A6** Idempotency on destructive operations (`cancel`, `delete`, `deleteAll`).
- **A7** Per-family logger namespace (`frontend:adapter:runtime`, `frontend:adapter:auth`, etc.). No PII in logs.
- **A8** `middleware/adapters/` never module-imports `agent_ui_adapter/`.
- **A9** SDK pin in JSDoc (`@sdk @langchain/langgraph-sdk ^0.0.x`).
- **A10** Per-family README under `adapters/<family>/README.md` listing port, current implementations, swap trigger.

## Translator Rules (T-Family)

- **T1** Imports only `wire/` and `trust-view/`. No SDK, no React, no I/O.
- **T2** Forward `trace_id` from input to every output shape.
- **T3** Zero-or-many output rule documented in JSDoc.
- **T4** Table-driven Vitest tests co-located as `*.test.ts`; one test per discriminated-union variant.

## Transport Rules (X-Family)

- **X1** `EventSource` only in `frontend/lib/transport/sse_client.ts`.
- **X2** Zod-parse on receive (`safeParse` against `AGUIEvent`); failures synthesize `RunErrorEvent` with `error_type: "wire_parse_error"`.
- **X3** `Last-Event-ID` resumption is non-optional.
- **X4** Heartbeat detection thresholds (15s send / 30s detect) documented and matched to Python `agent_ui_adapter/transport/heartbeat.py`.
- **X5** Backpressure: 100-event in-memory buffer; drop-oldest after that.
- **X6** BFF strips `Accept-Encoding` on streaming routes; sets `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache, no-transform`, `X-Accel-Buffering: no`, `Connection: keep-alive`; clears `Transfer-Encoding`.

## Composition Rules (C-Family)

- **C1** Single profile switch. `ARCHITECTURE_PROFILE` (or Python equivalent) appears only in composition root.
- **C2** Inject by port. Composition exports `buildAdapters()` returning a typed bag of port instances.
- **C3** React context provision. Adapters reach UI via a single `<AdapterProvider>` context; hooks read from it.
- **C4** Env reads only in composition. Adapters receive plain strings/numbers via constructor.
- **C5** Composition is the only file allowed to use `process.env.*` for adapter wiring.

## Browser Process Rules (B-Family)

- **B1** New components default to RSC. `'use client'` requires an inline justification comment.
- **B2** Pass Server Components to Client Components as `children`.
- **B3** Await `params`, `searchParams`, `cookies()`, `headers()` (Next 15 / React 19 contract).
- **B4** Server Actions for UI-triggered mutations; Route Handlers for SSE / external consumers.
- **B5** `cache: 'no-store'` is the default; `force-cache` only for non-user-scoped data.
- **B6** Route Handlers are composition adapters. Port calls and SSE byte-forward only -- no business `if/else`.
- **B7** Edge runtime opt-in only for `transport/edge_proxy.ts`.

## UI Rules (U-Family)

- **U1** RSC by default.
- **U2** Leaf `'use client'`. Push the boundary as far down the tree as possible.
- **U3** Sandboxed iframe (`<iframe sandbox="allow-scripts">` only) for generative UI.
- **U4** ARIA live region for streaming tokens: single persistent `<div role="log" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="false">`. Never `assertive`.
- **U5** Focus moves on route change only -- never on incoming tokens.
- **U6** `cn()` (`clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) for class merging. Template-string conditionals forbidden.
- **U7** shadcn primitives over custom-built. Wrap raw shadcn output (`components/ui/`) in `components/primitives/` for product-specific defaults.
- **U8** Design tokens via Tailwind v4 `@theme` blocks in `app/globals.css`. Semantic tokens (`--color-primary`), never raw hue values.
- **U_KBD** Composer textareas (S3.8.5 / F4) submit on `(metaKey || ctrlKey) && key === "Enter"`. `Shift+Enter` inserts a newline. The submit handler must call `e.preventDefault()` before invoking `onSend`.
- **U_IME** Composer submit branch is guarded by `!e.nativeEvent.isComposing` so an IME / kana / hangul `Enter` keystroke does not double-fire. Tested via a synthetic `KeyboardEvent` with `isComposing: true` in the unit suite.
- **U_AUTOSIZE** Composer textareas grow with content up to a documented max-rows (`6` rows by default for the chat composer) then scroll. Implementations: `rows` ref-based scrollHeight resize OR CSS `field-sizing: content`. Fixed-height textareas fail the F4 mobile-keyboard-friendly criterion.
- **U_LBL** Composer textareas have an associated `<label htmlFor>` OR an explicit `aria-label` (e.g. `"Message"`). Visually hidden labels (`sr-only`) satisfy the rule. Cross-checked by `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y/label-has-associated-control`.
- **U_FOCUS_NO_STEAL** Mount-time `taRef.current?.focus()` MUST NOT run while a sibling streaming-message live region (`role="log"`) is announcing tokens — that would steal focus from the screen reader mid-sentence (regression of `U5`). Either gate the mount focus on `!isStreaming`, or move it into the route-change `useEffect` that already moves focus on `params.threadId` change.

## Auth / Session Rules (S-Family)

- **S1** `AuthProvider.getAccessToken()` refreshes on `<60s` to expiry.
- **S2** BFF holds no cloud credentials (F-R9). All credential-bearing calls flow through `middleware/`.
- **S3** JWT verified server-side, never trusted client-side. Browser may read `Session.user_id` for display only.

## Observability Rules (O-Family)

- **O1** Telemetry never blocks SSE. `span()` / `start_span()` are non-blocking; failures swallowed.
- **O2** No PII in logs. Allowed: `trace_id`, `run_id`, `thread_id`, adapter name, error type, durations, status codes. Forbidden: tokens, memory content, LLM output text, user emails.
- **O3** Per-adapter logger namespace.
- **O4** `trace_id` propagated to every span (Langfuse trace external ID).

## Frontend Architectural Invariants (F-R1..F-R9)

- **F-R1** No domain logic in React components.
- **F-R2** SDK imports allowed only in `adapters/`.
- **F-R3** One interface per `ports/` module.
- **F-R4** BFF Route Handlers are composition adapters, not business logic.
- **F-R5** System prompts remain in `prompts/` as Jinja templates. No prompt strings in `.ts` / `.tsx`.
- **F-R6** `trust-view/` is read-only.
- **F-R7** Every emitted event must forward `trace_id` untouched.
- **F-R8** No SDK type may escape past an adapter boundary.
- **F-R9** BFF must never hold cloud credentials.

